**0.1 - What is Plan 9?  
0.1 - 什么是计划 9？**
------------------------------------------

  
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)  
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

Plan 9 is a research operating system from the same group who created UNIX at [Bell Labs Computing Sciences Research Center](https://web.archive.org/web/20150221121232/http://cm.bell-labs.com/cm/cs/alumni.html) (CSRC). It emerged in the late 1980s, and its early development coincided with continuing development of the later versions of [Research UNIX.](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Research_Unix) Plan 9 can be seen as an attempt to push some of the same ideas that informed UNIX [](https://www.westword.com/music/my-bus-wants-to-have-sex-with-your-bus-psychic-tvs-special-connection-to-denver-7415384)[_even further_](https://www.westword.com/music/my-bus-wants-to-have-sex-with-your-bus-psychic-tvs-special-connection-to-denver-7415384) into the era of networking and graphics. [Rob Pike](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rob_Pike) has described Plan 9 as "an argument" for simplicity and clarity, while others have described it as "UNIX, only moreso."  
Plan 9 是来自贝尔实验室计算科学研究中心 （CSRC） 创建 UNIX 的同一小组的研究操作系统。它出现在 1980 年代后期，其早期发展与后来版本的 Research UNIX 的持续发展相吻合。Plan 9 可以被看作是一次尝试，试图将一些相同的想法推入网络和图形时代，这些想法将 UNIX 进一步推向了网络和图形时代。Rob Pike 将 Plan 9 描述为简单明了的 “论据”，而其他人则将其描述为 “UNIX，只是更多”。

From _[The Use of Name Spaces in Plan 9:](http://doc.cat-v.org/plan_9/4th_edition/papers/names)_  
从计划 9 中名称空间的使用：

Plan 9 argues that given a few carefully implemented abstractions it is possible to produce a small operating system that provides support for the largest systems on a variety of architectures and networks.  
Plan 9 认为，只要有一些精心实现的抽象，就有可能产生一个小型操作系统，为各种架构和网络上的最大系统提供支持。

From the [](http://man.9front.org/1/intro)[intro(1)](http://man.9front.org/1/intro) man page:  
在手册页中 intro(1) ：

Plan 9 is a distributed computing environment assembled from separate machines acting as terminals, CPU servers, and file servers. A user works at a terminal, running a window system on a raster display. Some windows are connected to CPU servers; the intent is that heavy computing should be done in those windows but it is also possible to compute on the terminal. A separate file server provides file storage for terminals and CPU servers alike.  
计划 9 是一个分布式计算环境，由充当终端、CPU 服务器和文件服务器的独立计算机组装而成。用户在终端上工作，在光栅显示器上运行窗口系统。某些窗口连接到 CPU 服务器; 其目的是应该在这些窗口中完成繁重的计算，但也可以在终端上进行计算。单独的文件服务器为终端和 CPU 服务器提供文件存储。

The two most important ideas in Plan 9 are:  
计划 9 中最重要的两个想法是：

• [private namespaces](http://doc.cat-v.org/plan_9/4th_edition/papers/names) (each process constructs a unique view of the hierarchical file system)  
• 私有命名空间（每个进程构造分层文件系统的唯一视图）

• [file interfaces](http://man.9front.org/5/intro) (familiar from UNIX, but taken to the extreme: all resources in Plan 9 look like file systems)  
• 文件接口（熟悉 UNIX，但走极端：Plan 9 中的所有资源看起来都像文件系统）

Most everything else in the system falls out of these two basic ideas.  
系统中的大多数其他东西都不属于这两个基本思想。

_Plan 9 really pushes hard on some ideas that Unix has that haven’t really been fully developed, in particular, the notion that just about everything in the system is accessible through a file. In other words, things look like an ordinary disk file. So all the devices are controlled this way by means of ASCII strings, not complicated data structures. For example, you make network calls by writing an ASCII string, not the files. This notion is something that’s actually leaking quite fast.  
Plan 9 确实对 Unix 的一些尚未完全开发的想法进行了大力推动，特别是系统中几乎所有内容都可以通过文件访问的概念。换句话说，它看起来像一个普通的磁盘文件。因此，所有设备都是通过 ASCII 字符串而不是复杂的数据结构来控制的。例如，通过写入 ASCII 字符串（而不是文件）进行网络调用。这个概念实际上正在迅速泄露。_

_The second thing is sort of more subtle and sort of hard to appreciate until you’ve actually played with it. That is that the set of files an individual program can see depends on that program itself. In a standard kind of system, either with Unix remote file systems or Windows attached file systems, all the programs running in the machine see the same thing. In Plan 9, that’s adjustable per program. You can set up specialized name stations that are unique to a particular program. I mean, it’s not associated with the program itself but with the process, with the execution of the process.  
第二件事有点微妙，在你真正玩过它之前很难欣赏。也就是说，单个程序可以看到的文件集取决于该程序本身。在标准类型的系统中，无论是 Unix 远程文件系统还是 Windows 附加文件系统，机器中运行的所有程序都能看到相同的内容。在计划 9 中，这是每个程序的可调整。您可以设置特定程序独有的专用名称站。我的意思是，它与程序本身无关，而是与过程有关，与过程的执行有关。_

— Dennis Ritchie  — 丹尼斯 · 里奇

Read: [](http://man.9front.org/1/intro)[intro(1);](http://man.9front.org/1/intro) [](http://doc.cat-v.org/plan_9/4th_edition/papers/9)[_Plan 9 from Bell Labs;_](http://doc.cat-v.org/plan_9/4th_edition/papers/9) [](http://doc.cat-v.org/plan_9/1st_edition/designing_plan_9)[_Designing Plan 9,_](http://doc.cat-v.org/plan_9/1st_edition/designing_plan_9) originally delivered at the [UKUUG Conference in London, July 1990;](https://groups.google.com/forum/#!topic/uk.announce/wEUdLbrb_Uk) and [](fqa7.html)[_FQA 7 - System Management;_](fqa7.html) for a more detailed overview of Plan 9’s design.  
阅读： intro(1); 贝尔实验室的 Plan 9; 设计方案 9，最初于 1990 年 7 月在伦敦举行的 UKUUG 会议上发表; 和 FQA 7 - 系统管理; 以更详细地了解 Plan 9 的设计。

Today, Plan 9 continues in its original form, as well as in several derivatives and forks.  
今天，Plan 9 继续保持其原始形式，以及几个衍生品和分叉。

**The United States of Plan 9  
计划 9 的美国**

[Plan 9 from Bell Labs](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plan_9_from_Bell_Labs) — The original Plan 9. Effectively dead, all the developers have been run out of the Labs and/or are on display at Google.  
贝尔实验室的 Plan 9 — 最初的 Plan 9。实际上已经死了，所有的开发人员都已经从实验室中跑出来和 / 或在谷歌上展出。

[Plan 9 from User Space](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plan_9_from_User_Space) — Plan 9 userspace ported/imitated for UNIX (specifically OS X).  
来自用户空间的计划 9 — 为 UNIX（特别是 OS X）移植 / 模仿的计划 9 用户空间。

[9legacy](http://www.9legacy.org) — David du Colombier’s cherry picked collection of patches from various people/forks to Bell Labs Plan 9. (It is not a fork.)  
9legacy — David du Colombier 从不同的人 / 分支中精心挑选的补丁集合到 Bell Labs Plan 9。（它不是分叉。

[9atom](http://www.9atom.org) — Erik Quanstrom’s fork of Plan 9, maintained to Erik’s needs and occasionally pilfered by 9front.  
9atom — Erik Quanstrom 的 Plan 9 分支，根据 Erik 的需要进行维护，偶尔被 9front 窃取。

[9front](http://9front.org) — (that’s us) (we rule (we’re the tunnel snakes))  
9front — （那是我们） （我们统治（我们是隧道蛇））

[NIX](http://lsub.org/ls/nix.html) — High performance cloud computing is NIX — imploded in a cloud of political acrimony and retarded bureaucratic infighting.  
NIX——高性能云计算就是 NIK——在政治尖锐和官僚内斗的阴云中崩溃。

[NxM](http://nxm.coreboot.org/NxM) — A kernel for manycore systems — never spotted in the wild.  
NxM - 众核系统的内核 - 从未在野外被发现。

[Clive](http://lsub.org/ls/research.html) — A new operating system from Francisco J. Ballesteros, designed to generate grantwriting practice material and research projects for otherwise indolent students.  
克莱夫 — 弗朗西斯科 · 巴列斯特罗斯 （Francisco J. Ballesteros） 的新操作系统，旨在为其他懒惰的学生生成资助写作练习材料和研究项目。

[Akaros](http://akaros.cs.berkeley.edu/akaros-web/news.php) — Akaros is an open source, GPL-licensed operating system for manycore architectures. Has no bearing on anything but has attracted grant money.  
Akaros — Akaros 是一个开源的、GPL 许可的操作系统，适用于众核架构。与任何事情无关，但吸引了赠款。

[Harvey](http://harvey-os.org/) — Harvey is an effort to get the Plan 9 code working with gcc and clang.  
Harvey — Harvey 是为了让 Plan 9 代码与 gcc 和 clang 一起工作。

[Inferno](http://www.vitanuova.com/inferno/index.html) — Inferno is a distributed operating system started at Bell Labs, but is now developed and maintained by [Vita Nuova Holdings](http://www.vitanuova.com/) as free software. Just kidding it is not developed or maintained.  
Inferno — Inferno 是一个分布式操作系统，最初由 Bell Labs 开发，但现在由 Vita Nuova Holdings 作为免费软件开发和维护。开个玩笑，它没有开发或维护。

[ANTS](http://9gridchan.info) — Advanced Namespace Tools for Plan 9. ANTS is a collection of modifications and additional software which adds new namespace manipulation capabilities to Plan 9.  
ANTS — 计划 9 的高级命名空间工具。ANTS 是修改和附加软件的集合，它向 Plan 9 添加了新的命名空间操作功能。

Jehanne — Jehanne：Harvey：：William King Harvey：J. Edgar Hoover

Plan 9 Foundation — 现在提供 Plan 9 历史版本的下载。

### **0.1.1 - Plan 9 is not UNIX  
0.1.1 - 计划 9 不是 UNIX**

  
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

In the words of the [Bell Labs Plan 9 wiki:](https://9p.io/wiki/plan9/plan_9_wiki/fqa.html)  
用贝尔实验室计划 9 wiki 的话来说：

Plan 9 is not Unix. If you think of it as Unix, you may become frustrated when something doesn’t exist or when it works differently than you expected. If you think of it as Plan 9, however, you’ll find that most of it works very smoothly, and that there are some truly neat ideas that make things much cleaner than you have seen before.  
计划 9 不是 Unix。如果你把它看作是 Unix，你可能会感到沮丧，因为某些东西不存在，或者它的工作方式与你预期的不同。然而，如果你把它看作是第 9 号计划，你会发现它的大部分工作都非常顺利，并且有一些真正巧妙的想法，使事情比你以前看到的要干净得多。

Confusion is compounded by the fact that many UNIX commands exist on Plan 9 and behave in similar ways. In fact, some of Plan 9’s userland (such as the [](http://doc.cat-v.org/bell_labs/upas_mail_system)[upas](http://doc.cat-v.org/bell_labs/upas_mail_system) mail interface, the [](http://sam.cat-v.org)[sam](http://sam.cat-v.org) text editor, and the [](http://man.9front.org/1/rc)[rc](http://man.9front.org/1/rc) shell) are carried over directly from [Research UNIX 10th Edition.](https://web.archive.org/web/20170601063844/http://www.cs.bell-labs.com/10thEdMan) Further investigation reveals that many ideas found in Plan 9 were explored in more primitive form in the later editions of [Research UNIX.](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Research_Unix)  
由于许多 UNIX 命令存在于 Plan 9 上，并且其行为方式相似，这一事实使混淆更加复杂。事实上，Plan 9 的一些用户空间（如 upas 邮件界面、 sam 文本编辑器和 rc shell）是直接从 Research UNIX 10th Edition 继承过来的。进一步的调查表明，在计划 9 中发现的许多想法在后来的 Research UNIX 版本中以更原始的形式进行了探索。

However, Plan 9 is a completely new operating system that makes no attempt to conform to past prejudices. The point of the exercise (circa the late 1980s) was to avoid past problems and explore new territory. Plan 9 is not UNIX _for a reason._  
然而，Plan 9 是一个全新的操作系统，它没有试图符合过去的偏见。演习（大约在 1980 年代后期）的目的是避免过去的问题并探索新的领域。计划 9 不是 UNIX 是有原因的。

Read: [](http://wiki.9front.org/unix2plan9)[_UNIX to Plan 9 translation (wiki.9front.org),_](http://wiki.9front.org/unix2plan9) [](https://9p.io/wiki/plan9/Unix_to_Plan_9_command_translation/index.html)[_UNIX to Plan 9 command translation (9p.io),_](https://9p.io/wiki/plan9/Unix_to_Plan_9_command_translation/index.html) [](http://harmful.cat-v.org/cat-v/)[_UNIX Style, or cat -v Considered Harmful_](http://harmful.cat-v.org/cat-v/)  
阅读：UNIX 到计划 9 转换 （wiki.9front.org）、UNIX 到计划 9 命令转换 （9p.io）、UNIX 样式或 cat -v 被认为有害

#### **0.1.1.1 - Plan 9 is not plan9port  
0.1.1.1 - 计划 9 不是 plan9port**

[Plan 9 from User Space](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plan_9_from_user_space) (also known as plan9port or p9p) is a port of many Plan 9 from Bell Labs libraries and applications to UNIX-like operating systems. Currently it has been tested on a variety of operating systems including: Linux, Mac OS X, FreeBSD, NetBSD, OpenBSD, Solaris and SunOS.  
用户空间中的计划 9（也称为 plan9port 或 p9p）是从贝尔实验室库和应用程序到类 UNIX 操作系统的许多计划 9 的移植。目前，它已经在各种操作系统上进行了测试，包括：Linux、Mac OS X、FreeBSD、NetBSD、OpenBSD、Solaris 和 SunOS。

Plan9port consists of a combination of mostly unaltered Plan 9 userland utilities packaged alongside various attempts to imitate Plan 9’s kernel intefaces using miscellaneous available UNIX programs and commands. Some of the imitations are more successful than others. In all, plan9port does not accurately represent the experience of using actual Plan 9, but does provide enough functionality to make some users content with running acme on their Macbooks.  
Plan9port 由大部分未更改的 Plan 9 用户空间实用程序的组合组成，这些实用程序与使用各种可用的 UNIX 程序和命令模仿 Plan 9 内核接口的各种尝试打包在一起。有些模仿比其他模仿更成功。总而言之，plan9port 并不能准确代表使用实际 Plan 9 的体验，但确实提供了足够的功能，让一些用户满足于在他们的 Macbook 上运行 acme。

It is now being [slowly ported](https://9fans.topicbox.com/groups/9fans/T15127d7ddd5c7310/sam-and-samterm-in-go) to the Go programming language.  
它现在正在慢慢移植到 Go 编程语言中。

#### **0.1.1.2 - Plan 9 is not Inferno  
0.1.1.2 - 计划 9 不是地狱**

  
![](data:image/png;base64,)

[Inferno](http://www.vitanuova.com/inferno/index.html) is a distributed operating system also created at Bell Labs, but which is now developed and maintained by [Vita Nuova Holdings](http://www.vitanuova.com/) as free software. It employs many ideas from Plan 9 (Inferno does share some compatible interfaces with Plan 9, including the [9P/Styx](http://9p.cat-v.org) protocol), but is a completely different OS. Many users new to Plan 9 find out about Inferno and immediately decide to abandon Plan 9 and its opaque user interface for this obviously "more advanced" sibling, but usually abandon that, too, upon first contact with Inferno’s Tk GUI. Notable exceptions duly noted.  
Inferno 是一个分布式操作系统，也是由 Bell Labs 创建的，但现在由 Vita Nuova Holdings 作为免费软件开发和维护。它采用了 Plan 9 的许多想法（Inferno 确实与 Plan 9 共享一些兼容的接口，包括 9P/Styx 协议），但是一个完全不同的操作系统。许多刚接触 Plan 9 的用户发现了 Inferno，并立即决定放弃 Plan 9 及其不透明的用户界面，转而使用这个明显 “更高级” 的兄弟姐妹，但通常也会在第一次接触 Inferno 的 Tk GUI 时放弃它。值得注意的例外情况已适当指出。

See: [http://www.xs4all.nl/~mechiel/inferno/](https://web.archive.org/web/20100531143216/http://www.xs4all.nl/~mechiel/inferno/)  
请参见：http://www.xs4all.nl/~mechiel/inferno/

### **0.1.3 - Plan 9 is not for you  
0.1.3 - 计划 9 不适合您**

**Let’s be perfectly honest.** Many features that today’s "computer experts" consider to be essential to computing (JavaScript, CSS, HTML5, etc.) either did not exist when Plan 9 was abandoned by its creators, or were purposely left out of the operating system. You might find this to be an unacceptable obstacle to adopting Plan 9 into your daily workflow. If you cannot imagine a use for a computer that does not involve a web browser, Plan 9 may not be for you.  
说实话。今天的 “计算机专家” 认为对计算至关重要的许多功能（JavaScript、CSS、HTML5 等）要么在 Plan 9 被其创建者抛弃时不存在，要么被故意排除在操作系统之外。您可能会发现这是将计划 9 纳入日常工作流程的不可接受的障碍。如果您无法想象不涉及 Web 浏览器的计算机的用途，那么 Plan 9 可能不适合您。

See: [http://harmful.cat-v.org/software/](http://harmful.cat-v.org/software/)  
请参见：http://harmful.cat-v.org/software/

On the other hand, the roaring 2020s have seen Plan 9 sprout a substantial presence on social media, so if you’re here for that, YMMV.  
另一方面，咆哮的 2020 年代见证了 Plan 9 在社交媒体上的大量存在，所以如果你来这里，YMMV。

**0.2 - Why Plan 9?  
0.2 - 为什么选择计划 9？**
----------------------------------------

You may ask yourself, well, how did I get here? In the words of Plan 9 contributor [Russ Cox:](http://swtch.com)  
你可能会问自己，好吧，我是怎么来到这里的？用 Plan 9 贡献者 Russ Cox 的话来说：

Why Plan 9 indeed. Isn’t Plan 9 just another Unix clone? Who cares?  
为什么是 Plan 9。Plan 9 不就是另一个 Unix 克隆吗？谁在乎啊？

Plan 9 presents a consistent and easy to use interface. Once you’ve settled in, there are very few surprises here. After I switched to Linux from Windows 3.1, I noticed all manner of inconsistent behavior in Windows 3.1 that Linux did not have. Switching to Plan 9 from Linux highlighted just as much in Linux.  
Plan 9 提供了一个一致且易于使用的界面。一旦你安顿下来，这里就没有什么惊喜了。在我从 Windows 3.1 切换到 Linux 后，我注意到 Windows 3.1 中存在 Linux 所没有的各种不一致行为。从 Linux 切换到 Plan 9 在 Linux 中同样突出了这一点。

One reason Plan 9 can do this is that the Plan 9 group has had the luxury of having an entire system, so problems can be fixed and features added where they belong, rather than where they can be. For example, there is no tty driver in the kernel. The window system handles the nuances of terminal input.  
Plan 9 能够做到这一点的一个原因是，Plan 9 小组拥有整个系统的奢侈，因此可以修复问题并将功能添加到它们所属的地方，而不是它们可以在的地方。例如，内核中没有 tty 驱动程序。窗口系统处理终端输入的细微差别。

If Plan 9 was just a really clean Unix clone, it might be worth using, or it might not. The neat things start happening with user-level file servers and per-process namespace. In Unix, /dev/tty refers to the current window’s output device, and means different things to different processes. This is a special hack enabled by the kernel for a single file. Plan 9 provides full-blown per-process namespaces. In Plan 9 /dev/cons also refers to the current window’s output device, and means different things to different processes, but the window system (or telnet daemon, or ssh daemon, or whatever) arranges this, and does the same for /dev/mouse, /dev/text (the contents of the current window), etc.  
如果 Plan 9 只是一个非常干净的 Unix 克隆，它可能值得使用，也可能不值得使用。整洁的事情开始发生在用户级文件服务器和每个进程命名空间上。在 Unix 中，/dev/tty 指的是当前窗口的输出设备，对不同的进程有不同的含义。这是内核为单个文件启用的特殊 hack。计划 9 提供了成熟的每个进程命名空间。在 Plan 9 中，/dev/cons 也指当前窗口的输出设备，对不同的进程有不同的含义，但窗口系统（或 telnet 守护进程，或 ssh 守护进程，或其他什么）对此进行了安排，并且对 /dev/mouse、/dev/text（当前窗口的内容）等执行相同的操作。

Since pieces of file tree can be provided by user-level servers, the kernel need not know about things like DOS’s FAT file system or GNU/Linux’s EXT2 file system or NFS, etc. Instead, user-level servers provide this functionality when desired. In Plan 9, even FTP is provided as a file server: you run ftpfs and the files on the server appear in /n/ftp.  
由于文件树的片段可以由用户级服务器提供，因此内核不需要知道 DOS 的 FAT 文件系统或 GNU/Linux 的 EXT2 文件系统或 NFS 等。相反，用户级服务器会在需要时提供此功能。在计划 9 中，甚至 FTP 也作为文件服务器提供：运行 ftpfs，服务器上的文件显示在 /n/ftp 中。

We need not stop at physical file systems, though. Other file servers synthesize files that represent other resources. For example, upas/fs presents your mail box as a file tree at /mail/fs/mbox. This models the recursive structure of MIME messages especially well.  
不过，我们不必止步于物理文件系统。其他文件服务器合成表示其他资源的文件。例如，upas/fs 将您的邮箱显示为 /mail/fs/mbox 中的文件树。这特别好地模拟了 MIME 消息的递归结构。

As another example, cdfs presents an audio or data CD as a file system, one file per track. If it’s a writable CD, copying new files into the /mnt/cd/wa or /mnt/cd/wd directories does create new audio or data tracks. Want to fixate the CD as audio or data? Remove one of the directories.  
再举一个例子，cdfs 将音频或数据 CD 作为文件系统呈现，每个轨道一个文件。如果是可写 CD，则将新文件复制到 /mnt/cd/wa 或 /mnt/cd/wd 目录中会创建新的音频或数据轨道。想要将 CD 固定为音频或数据吗？删除其中一个目录。

Plan 9 fits well with a networked environment, files and directory trees can be imported from other machines, and all resources are files or directory trees, it’s easy to share resources. Want to use a different machine’s sound card? Import its /dev/audio. Want to debug processes that run on another machine? Import its /proc. Want to use a network interface on another machine? Import its /net. And so on.  
方案 9 非常适合网络环境，可以从其他机器导入文件和目录树，并且所有资源都是文件或目录树，很容易共享资源。想要使用其他机器的声卡？导入其 /dev/audio。想要调试在另一台计算机上运行的进程？导入其 /proc. 想要在另一台计算机上使用网络接口？导入其 /net。等等。

Russ Cox  拉斯 · 考克斯

### **0.2.3 - Why did Plan 9’s creators give up on Plan 9?  
0.2.3 - 为什么 Plan 9 的创建者放弃了 Plan 9？**

  
![](https://fqa.9front.org/belllabs.jpg)

All of the people who worked on Plan 9 have moved on from Bell Labs and/or no longer work on Plan 9. Various reasons have been articulated by various people.  
所有参与 Plan 9 的人都离开了贝尔实验室和 / 或不再从事 Plan 9 的工作。不同的人已经阐明了各种原因。

[Russ Cox: 拉斯 · 考克斯（Russ Cox）：](http://russ.cox.usethis.com)

I ran Plan 9 from Bell Labs as my day to day work environment until around 2002. By then two facts were painfully clear. First, the Internet was here to stay; and second, Plan 9 had no hope of keeping up with web browsers. Porting Mozilla to Plan 9 was far too much work, so instead I ported almost all the Plan 9 user level software to FreeBSD, Linux, and OS X.  
直到 2002 年左右，我才将贝尔实验室的 Plan 9 作为我的日常工作环境。到那时，有两个事实非常清楚。首先，互联网将继续存在; 其次，Plan 9 没有希望跟上 Web 浏览器的步伐。将 Mozilla 移植到 Plan 9 的工作量太大了，所以我将几乎所有的 Plan 9 用户级软件移植到 FreeBSD、Linux 和 OS X 上。

Russ Cox [(again):](http://marc.info/?l=9fans&m=126697423223383) 拉斯 · 考克斯（再次）：

The standard set up for a Plan 9 aficionado here seems to be a Mac or Linux machine running Plan 9 from User Space to get at sam, acme, and the other tools. Rob, Ken, Dave, and I use Macs as our desktop machines, but we’re a bit of an exception. Most Google engineers use Linux machines, and I know of quite a few ex-Bell Labs people who are happy to be using sam or acme on those machines. My own setup is two screens. The first is a standard Mac desktop with non-Plan 9 apps and a handful of 9terms, and the second is a full-screen acme for getting work done. On Linux I do the same but the first screen is a Linux desktop running rio (formerly dhog’s 8½).  
这里为 Plan 9 爱好者设置的标准似乎是一台 Mac 或 Linux 机器，从用户空间运行 Plan 9 以获取 sam、acme 和其他工具。Rob、Ken、Dave 和我使用 Mac 作为台式电脑，但我们有点例外。大多数 Google 工程师都使用 Linux 机器，我知道有不少前贝尔实验室的人乐于在这些机器上使用 sam 或 acme。我自己的设置是两个屏幕。第一个是标准的 Mac 桌面，带有非 Plan 9 应用程序和少数 9 个术语，第二个是完成工作的全屏极致。在 Linux 上，我做同样的事情，但第一个屏幕是运行 rio（以前称为 dhog 的 81/2）的 Linux 桌面。

More broadly, every few months I tend to get an email from someone who is happy to have just discovered that sam is still maintained and available for modern systems. A lot of the time these are people who only used sam on Unix, never on Plan 9. The plan9port.tgz file was downloaded from 2,522 unique IP addresses in 2009, which I suspect is many more than Plan 9 itself. In that sense, it’s really nice to see the tools getting a much wider exposure than they used to.  
更广泛地说，每隔几个月，我就会收到一封电子邮件，他很高兴刚刚发现 sam 仍在维护并可用于现代系统。很多时候，这些人只在 Unix 上使用 sam，而从未在 Plan 9 上使用过。2009 年，plan9port.tgz 文件是从 2,522 个唯一 IP 地址下载的，我怀疑这比 Plan 9 本身要多得多。从这个意义上说，很高兴看到这些工具获得了比以前更广泛的曝光。

I haven’t logged into a real Plan 9 system in many years, but I use 9vx occasionally when I want to remind myself how a real Plan 9 tool worked. It’s always nice to be back, however briefly.  
我已经很多年没有登录过真正的 Plan 9 系统了，但当我想提醒自己真正的 Plan 9 工具是如何工作的时，我偶尔会使用 9vx。回来总是很高兴的，无论多么短暂。

Russ  拉斯

Russ Cox [continues:](http://marc.info/?l=9fans&m=126700061820789) Russ Cox 继续说道：

> Can you briefly tell us why you (Russ, Rob, Ken and Dave)  
> 你能简单告诉我们为什么你（Russ、Rob、Ken 和 Dave）吗？

> no longer use Plan9 ?  
> 不再使用 Plan9 ？

> Because of missing apps or because of missing driver for your hardware ?  
> 由于缺少应用程序或缺少硬件驱动程序？

> And do you still use venti ?  
> 你还在用通风口吗？

Operating systems and programming languages have strong network effects: it helps to use the same system that everyone around you is using. In my group at MIT, that meant FreeBSD and C++. I ran Plan 9 for the first few years I was at MIT but gave up, because the lack of a shared system made it too hard to collaborate. When I switched to FreeBSD, I ported all the Plan 9 libraries and tools so I could keep the rest of the user experience.  
操作系统和编程语言具有很强的网络效应：它有助于使用您周围每个人都在使用的相同系统。在我在麻省理工学院的小组中，这意味着 FreeBSD 和 C++。在麻省理工学院的最初几年里，我运行了 Plan 9，但放弃了，因为缺乏共享系统使得协作变得太困难了。当我切换到 FreeBSD 时，我移植了所有 Plan 9 的库和工具，这样我就可以保留其余的用户体验。

I still use venti, in that I still maintain the venti server that takes care of backups for my old group at MIT. It uses the plan9port venti, vbackup, and vnfs, all running on FreeBSD. The venti server itself was my last real Plan 9 installation. It’s Coraid hardware, but I stripped the software and had installed my own Plan 9 kernel to run venti on it directly. But before I left MIT, the last thing I did was reinstall the machine using FreeBSD so that others could help keep it up to date.  
我仍然使用 venti，因为我仍然维护 venti 服务器，它负责我在麻省理工学院的旧小组的备份。它使用 plan9port venti、vbackup 和 vnfs，它们都运行在 FreeBSD 上。venti 服务器本身是我最后一次真正的 Plan 9 安装。这是 Coraid 硬件，但我剥离了软件并安装了我自己的 Plan 9 内核来直接在上面运行 venti。但在我离开麻省理工学院之前，我做的最后一件事就是使用 FreeBSD 重新安装机器，以便其他人可以帮助它保持最新状态。

If I wasn’t interacting with anyone else it’d be nice to keep using Plan 9. But it’s also nice to be able to use off the shelf software instead of reinventing wheels (9fans runs on Linux) and to have good hardware support done by other people (I can shut my laptop and it goes to sleep, and even better, when I open it again, it wakes up!). Being able to get those things and still keep most of the Plan 9 user experience by running Plan 9 from User Space is a compromise, but one that works well for me.  
如果我不与其他人互动，那么继续使用 Plan 9 会很好。但是，能够使用现成的软件而不是重新发明轮子（9fans 在 Linux 上运行）并由其他人提供良好的硬件支持（我可以关闭我的笔记本电脑，它进入睡眠状态，甚至更好的是，当我再次打开它时，它会醒来！通过从用户空间运行 Plan 9 来获得这些东西并仍然保留大部分 Plan 9 用户体验是一种妥协，但对我来说效果很好。

Russ  拉斯

[Rob Pike: 罗伯 · 派克：](http://marc.info/?l=9fans&m=126704318227120)

What Russ says is true but for me it was simpler. I used Plan 9 as my local operating system for a year or so after joining Google, but it was just too inconvenient to live on a machine without a C++ compiler, without good NFS and SSH support, and especially without a web browser. I switched to Linux but found it very buggy (the main problem was most likely a bad graphics board and/or driver, but still) and my main collaborator (Robert Griesemer) had done the ground work to get a Mac working as a primary machine inside Google, and Russ had plan9port up, so I pushed plan9port onto the Mac and have been there ever since, quite happily. Nowadays Apples are officially supported so it’s become easy, workwise.  
Russ 说的是真的，但对我来说更简单。加入 Google 后，我使用 Plan 9 作为我的本地操作系统一年左右，但是在没有 C++ 编译器、没有良好的 NFS 和 SSH 支持，尤其是没有 Web 浏览器的机器上生活太不方便了。我切换到 Linux，但发现它非常有问题（主要问题很可能是显卡和 / 或驱动程序坏了，但仍然如此），我的主要合作者 （Robert Griesemer） 已经做了基础工作，让 Mac 作为 Google 内部的主机工作，Russ 已经启动了 plan9port，所以我将 plan9port 推到了 Mac 上，从那时起就一直在那里， 非常高兴。如今，Apple 得到了官方支持，因此在工作方面变得容易。

I miss a lot of what Plan 9 did for me, but the concerns at work override that.  
我很怀念 Plan 9 为我所做的很多事情，但工作中的担忧压倒了这一点。

这就是我的朋友们，这就是为什么 MP-3 起飞而不是更好的原因

follow-on system we were on the cusp of getting out the door.  
后续系统，我们正处于走出大门的风口浪尖。

-rob - 抢

P.S. No, I don’t have the music any more. Too sad to keep.  
P.S. 不，我没有音乐了。太难过了，无法保持。

### **0.2.4 - What is the deal with Plan 9’s weird license?  
0.2.4 - Plan 9 的奇怪许可证是怎么回事？**

  
![](https://fqa.9front.org/intellectualproperty.jpg)

Over the years Plan 9 has been released under various licenses, to the consternation of many.  
多年来，Plan 9 已在各种许可下发布，这让许多人感到震惊。

The first edition, released in 1992, was made available only to universities. The process for acquiring the software was convoluted and prone to clerical error. Many potential users had trouble obtaining it within a reasonable time frame and many complaints were voiced on the eventual [Plan 9 Internet mailing list.](fqa2.html#2.2.2)  
第一版于 1992 年发布，仅供大学使用。获取软件的过程错综复杂，容易出现笔误。许多潜在用户在合理的时间范围内无法获得它，并且在最终的 Plan 9 互联网邮件列表中表达了许多抱怨。

The second edition, released in 1995 in book-and-CD form under a relatively standard commercial license, was available via mailorder as well as through a special telephone number for a price of approximately $350 USD. It was certainly easier to acquire than the first edition, but many potential users still complained that the price was too high and that the license was too restrictive.  
第二版于 1995 年在相对标准的商业许可下以书籍和 CD 形式发行，可通过邮购和特殊电话号码获得，价格约为 350 美元。它当然比第一版更容易获得，但许多潜在用户仍然抱怨价格太高，许可证限制性太强。

#### **0.2.4.1 - Richard Stallman hates the Plan Nine license (circa 2000)  
0.2.4.1 - 理查德 · 斯托曼（Richard Stallman）讨厌九号计划许可证（约 2000 年）**

In the year 2000, the third edition of Plan 9 was finally released under a custom "open source" license, the [Plan 9 License.](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plan_9_from_Bell_Labs#History) [Richard Stallman](https://stallman.org/) was not impressed:  
2000 年，Plan 9 的第三版终于在自定义的 “开源” 许可证下发布，即 Plan 9 许可证。理查德 · 斯托曼（Richard Stallman）对此不以为然：

When I saw the announcement that the Plan Nine software had been released as "open source", I wondered whether it might be free software as well. After studying the license, my conclusion was that it is not free; the license contains several restrictions that are totally unacceptable for the Free Software Movement. (See [http://www.gnu.org/philosophy/free-sw.html](http://www.gnu.org/philosophy/free-sw.html)  
当我看到 Plan Nine 软件作为 “开源” 发布的公告时，我想知道它是否也可能是自由软件。在研究了许可证之后，我的结论是它不是免费的; 该许可证包含一些限制，这些限制对于自由软件运动来说是完全不可接受的。（见 http://www.gnu.org/philosophy/free-sw.html

Read more here:  在这里阅读更多内容：

[http://www.linuxtoday.com/developer/2000070200704OPLFSW](http://www.linuxtoday.com/developer/2000070200704OPLFSW)

#### **0.2.4.2 - Theo de Raadt hates the Plan 9 license (circa 2003)  
0.2.4.2 - Theo de Raadt 讨厌 Plan 9 许可证（大约 2003 年）**

In the year 2002, the fourth edition of Plan 9 was released under the [Lucent Public License.](http://git.9front.org/plan9front/plan9front/HEAD/lib/legal/lpl/f.html) This time, Theo de Raadt was not impressed:  
2002 年，Plan 9 的第四版在朗讯公共许可证下发布。这一次，西奥 · 德 · 拉德（Theo de Raadt）没有留下深刻的印象：

The new license is utterly unacceptable for use in a BSD project.  
在 BSD 项目中使用新许可证是完全不可接受的。

Actually, I am astounded that the OSI would declare such a license acceptable.  
实际上，我很惊讶 OSI 会宣布这样的许可证是可以接受的。

That is not a license which makes it free. It is a *contract* with consequences; let me be clear -- it is a contract with consequences that I am unwilling to accept.  
这不是一个使它免费的许可证。这是一份有后果的 * 合同 *; 让我明确一点——这是一份我不愿意接受的后果的合同。

Read more here:  在这里阅读更多内容：

[http://9fans.net/archive/2003/06/270](http://marc.info/?l=9fans&m=111558887521594)

#### **0.2.4.3 - Everyone hates the Plan 9 license (circa 2014)  
0.2.4.3 - 每个人都讨厌 Plan 9 许可证（大约 2014 年）**

In 2014, portions of the Plan 9 source code were again re-licensed, this time under the [GPLv2,](http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-2.0.html) for distribution with the [University of California, Berkeley’s](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/University_of_California,_Berkeley) [Akaros](http://akaros.cs.berkeley.edu/akaros-web/) operating system. Predictably, various parties were not impressed.  
2014 年，Plan 9 的部分源代码再次获得重新授权，这次是在 GPLv2 下，与加州大学伯克利分校的 Akaros 操作系统一起分发。不出所料，各方都没有留下深刻的印象。

Russ Cox tried to make sense of the situation by commenting in a [Hacker News thread:](https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=7232511)  
Russ Cox 试图通过在 Hacker News 帖子中发表评论来理解这种情况：

When you ask "why did big company X make strange choice Y regarding licensing or IP", 99 times out of 100 the answer is"lawyers". If the Plan 9 group had had its way, Plan 9 would have been released for free under a trivial MIT-like license (the one used for other pieces of code, like the one true awk) in 2003 instead of creating the Lucent Public License. Or in 2000 instead of creating the "Plan 9 License". Or in 1995 instead of as a $350 book+CD that came with a license for use by an entire "organization". Or in 1992 instead of being a limited academic release.  
当你问 “为什么大公司 X 在许可或知识产权方面做出奇怪的选择 Y” 时，100 次中有 99 次的答案是 “律师”。如果 Plan 9 小组如愿以偿，Plan 9 将在 2003 年以类似 MIT 的普通许可证（用于其他代码的许可证，例如真正的 awk）免费发布，而不是创建朗讯公共许可证。或者在 2000 年而不是创建“Plan 9 许可证”。或者在 1995 年，而不是作为 350 美元的书籍 + CD，附带许可证供整个“组织” 使用。或者在 1992 年，而不是有限的学术版本。

Thankfully I am not at Lucent anymore and am not privy to the tortured negotiations that ended up at the obviously inelegant compromise of "The University of California, Berkeley, has been authorised by Alcatel-Lucent to release all Plan 9 software previously governed by the Lucent Public License, Version 1.02 under the GNU General Public License, Version 2." But the odds are overwhelming that the one-word answer is "lawyers".  
值得庆幸的是，我不再在朗讯工作了，也不再参与这场折磨人的谈判，这些谈判最终以明显不优雅的妥协告终：“加州大学伯克利分校已获得阿尔卡特朗讯的授权，可以在 GNU 通用公共许可证第 2 版下发布所有以前受朗讯公共许可证 1.02 版管理的 Plan 9 软件。但一个词的答案是 “律师” 的可能性是压倒性的。

Some have suggested that confusion about licensing may have contributed to Plan 9’s failure to supplant UNIX in the wider computing world.  
一些人认为，对许可的混淆可能是导致 Plan 9 未能在更广泛的计算世界中取代 UNIX 的原因。

0.2.4.4 - 赞扬 9FRONT 的大胆行动，回复：许可**

#### **0.2.4.5 - Everyone loves the Plan 9 license (circa 2021)  
0.2.4.5 - 每个人都喜欢 Plan 9 许可证（大约 2021 年）**

In 2021, the [Plan 9 Foundation](http://9pf.org) (aka P9F—no relation) convinced Nokia to [re-license](https://9fans.topicbox.com/groups/9fans/Tf20bce89ef96d4b6-M63f81768e4ffdfa4df402ec5) all historical editions of the Plan9 source code under the MIT Public License.  
2021 年，Plan 9 基金会（又名 P9F——无关系）说服诺基亚根据 MIT 公共许可证重新许可 Plan9 源代码的所有历史版本。

As a consequence, _all_ of 9front is now provided under the MIT License unless otherwise indicated.  
因此，除非另有说明，否则所有 9front 现在都是根据 MIT 许可证提供的。

Re-read: [](http://git.9front.org/plan9front/plan9front/HEAD/lib/legal/mit/f.html)[/lib/legal/mit](http://git.9front.org/plan9front/plan9front/HEAD/lib/legal/mit/f.html)  重读： /lib/legal/mit
